               <msContents>
                  <summary>Commentary on the Gospels, volume 1.  P. 4: Notice of donation to the library from Emperor Haile Selassie in 1936 AM.  Commentaries in Amharic and Ge'ez. Pp. 5-55: Commentary on the Eusebian canon. Pp. 56-67: Commentary on the Introduction to the Gospel of Matthew. Pp. 68-250: Commentary on the Gospel of Matthew. P. 190 contains two seals of the administrator of the church; p. 250 contains another seal. Pp. 250-265: Commentary on the Gospel of Mark. P. 266: Introductory material for the Gospel Luke, incomplete at the end. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="3r" to="28r">fol. 3r-28r</locus>
                     <title>Commentary on the introduction to the gospels</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="am">ይህን ፡ መጽሐፍ ፡ አሞንዮስ ፡ አውሳብዮስ ፡ ተናግረውታል ፡ እሊህስ ፡ መነሳታቸው ፡ ከ፫፻በሬት ፡ ነው ። በኋላ ፡ ቢሉ ፡ በሬት ፡ ነው ።</incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <locus from="28v" to="168v">fol. 28v-168v</locus>
                     <title>Commentary on the gospel of Matthew</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="am">ይህ ፡ ቃል ፡ የ፫፻ነው ፡ ጥንተ ፡ ነገሩ ፡ እንደምን ፡ ነው ። ቢሉ ፡ እግዚአብሔር ፡ እምቅድመ ፡ ዓለም ፡ በልብ ፡ የመከረውን ፡ በነቢያት ፡ ያናገረውን ፡ ለመፈጸም ፡ ሥጋ ፡ ሆነ ፡</incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                     <locus from="169r" to="176r">fol. 169r-176r</locus>
                     <title>Commentary on the gospel of Mark</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="am">ማርቆስ ፡ ማለት ፡ ንህብ ፡ ማለት ፡ ነው ። ንህብ ፡ ከሁሉ ፡ እንዲቀስም ፡ እሱም ፡ እስቀድሞ ፡ ከጌታ ፡ ኋላ ፡ ከሐዋርያት ፡ ተ፡ምሯልና ፡</incipit>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                     <locus target="#176v">Fol. 176v</locus>
                     <title type="incomplete">Commentary on the gospel of Luke</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="am">ሉቃስ ፡ ማለት ፡ ጠቢብ ፡ ማለት ፡ ነው ፡ ቀድሞ ፡ ዓቃቤ ፡ ሥራይ ፡ ዘሥጋ ፡ ነበረ ፡ ኋላ ፡ ዓቃቤ ፡ ሥራይ ፡ ዘነፍስ ፡ ሁይል ።</incipit>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
